   "source": [
    "# RetinaGuard — Train & Evaluate on APTOS 2019 (Colab T4)\n",
    "\n",
    "Run top-to-bottom. End result: real trained weights (`retinoguard_best.pth`) plus a full metrics report (accuracy, per-class precision/recall/F1, one-vs-rest AUC, quadratic weighted kappa, confusion matrix + ROC images).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before you start:**\n",
    "1. Runtime → Change runtime type → **GPU (T4)**.\n",
    "2. Have your `kaggle.json` API token ready (Kaggle → Account → Create New API Token).\n",
    "3. Accept the APTOS 2019 competition rules once at https://www.kaggle.com/c/aptos2019-blindness-detection/rules (required for the download to work).\n",
    "4. Set `GITHUB_REPO` below to your RetinaGuard repo URL, **or** upload the `ml/` folder manually (see the alt cell)."
   ]
  },
